        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>From M51, we expect linewidths of 8 to 10 km/s. Our motivation for this science goal is a map of CO integrated intensity (~column density) to trace morphology of the cold gas at matched resolution to our polarization measurements. Since our time request is not sensitivity-limited, we select a correlator configuration with adequate velocity resolution to construct maps of the velocity field and velocity dispersion in case they are useful. The full velocity width of HI emission in NGC1566 is ~300km/s (Kilborn et al. 2005), which fits comfortably within the range covered by our correlator setup. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The purpose of this science goal is to obtain a map of the molecular gas surface density with matched resolution to our polarisation data. The angular resolution is therefore the same as the resolution that we target in SGs 1 &amp; 2. Although the CO(3-2) emission in our fields may be intrinsically more extended than 5 arcseconds, these spatial scales will not be present in our polarisation data. We therefore do not request ACA or TP observations.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our estimate for the CO(3-2) peak brightness in NGC1566 is based on (i) the CO(3-2) emission detected by ALMA at the centre of NGC1566 (Combes et al. 2014) and (ii) a high resolution CO(1-0) cube of M51 that we have smoothed to the requested resolution for NGC1566 and rescaled assuming CO(3-2)/CO(1-0) = 0.5. Both approaches suggest that the typical CO(3-2) brightness of relatively faint emission in our 1.4" beam will be ~0.5K. From M51, we expect linewidths of 8 to 10 km/s. 






</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
